org.vesselonline.test
Class WebResource

java.lang.Object
  org.vesselonline.test.WebResource

public class WebResource
extends java.lang.Object

Represents a single web resource, typically defined by the HTML you would receive by requesting the resource's URL with a web client. Contains representations for various HTML elements, including tables and forms, that might make up such a page.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Steven Handy
See Also:
WebSite, WebForm

Constructor Detail

WebResource

public WebResource(java.lang.String name,
                   java.lang.String url,
                   java.lang.String frame,
                   java.lang.String h1)
Constructor creates a new WebResource with the basic information provided. Descriptions for a new resource are defined in the jWebUnitSiteDescription XML file.

Parameters:
name - Name of the web resource.
url - URL defining the location of the web resource, relative to the base URL of the web site this resource is a part of. May contain a query string in addition to the resource path and file name.
frame - Name of the frame this resource appears in on the web site.
h1 - Top-level heading for the resource, if one exists.
Method Detail

getName

public java.lang.String getName()
Gets the name assigned to this resource. This is an arbitrary designation, but must be unique among the resources for the web site.

Returns:
Name of the resource.

getFrame

public java.lang.String getFrame()
Gets the name of the frame in which this resource appears in the web site. The frame is used to derive the "template" set of tests for all resources that appear in that frame.

Returns:
Name of the frame in which this resource appears.

getUrl

public java.lang.String getUrl()
Gets the URL for the resource. The URL is relative to the base URL for the web site and may include a query string.

Returns:
URL as a string for the resource.

getH1

public java.lang.String getH1()
Gets the top-level heading for the resource. This field may not be present.

Returns:
Text of the top-level heading for the resource.

public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> getImgs()

getText

public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> getText()
Gets a collection of all the text strings that should be verified to be present in this resource. The strings may contain HTML markup.

Returns:
ArrayList of strings, each item containing text to be verified in the HTML of the resource.

getLinks

public java.util.Set<java.util.Map.Entry<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>> getLinks()
Gets the set of HTML links that are defined for this resource. Valid types of links include "txt" and "img".

Returns:
Set of Map.Entry objects containing information about links defined for this resource. The format of the entry is key=link text|image URL, value=type.

getTables

public java.util.Set<java.util.Map.Entry<java.lang.String,java.lang.String[]>> getTables()
Gets the set of HTML tables that are defined for this resource. Tables are identified by their id or summary attribute text. Their content is defined by an array of strings that should be present in the table.

Returns:
Set of Map.Entry objects containing information about tables defined for this resource. The format of the entry is key=summary, value=array of strings in the table.

getForms

public java.util.Set<java.util.Map.Entry<java.lang.String,WebForm>> getForms()
Gets the set a HTML forms that are defined for this resource. Forms are identified by their id attribute text.

Returns:
Set of Map.Entry objects containing information about forms defined for this resource. The format of the entry is key=id, value=WebForm for that form.
